  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A Chinese rocket falls into the Indian Ocean",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "NASA says that the rocket sent into space by the Chinese space agency on July 24 crashed into the Indian Ocean.",
        "NASA also says that China has not said anything about which region of the Indian Ocean the rocket crashed into. NASA scientists also point out that if the rocket had crashed in a populated place, there would have been a great destruction.",
        "China is building a space station in Earth orbit called 'Tiangon'. The construction of the space station is done by bringing its parts (modules) into space by rockets and assembling them. Chinese astronauts take turns staying in space and making deliveries to the space station.",
        "The China Space Agency expects to complete the Tiangong space station this year.",
        "Last July 24, several modules were successfully sent into space to connect to the space station.",
        "Today (31), the 'Long March B8Y3' rocket and its parts, which carried the modules into space, crashed dangerously back to earth."
      ],
